vulnerability.name: USN-6401-1
vulnerability.description: It was discovered that FreeRDP did not properly manage certain inputs. A malicious server could use this issue to cause FreeRDP clients to crash, resulting in a denial of service, or possibly obtain sensitive  information. (CVE-2023-39350, CVE-2023-39351,  CVE-2023-39353,  CVE-2023-39354, CVE-2023-40181, CVE-2023-40188, CVE-2023-40589)  It was discovered that FreeRDP did not properly manage certain inputs. A malicious server could use this issue to cause FreeRDP clients to crash, resulting in a denial of service, or possibly execute arbitrary code. (CVE-2023-40186, CVE-2023-40567, CVE-2023-40569)

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in FreeRDP.
